OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FDry with any early morning
OL,6,Fcloud soon burning off to leave a very
OL,7,Fwarm day with sunny spells, However,
OL,8,Fthe cloud could be slower to clear
OL,9,Facross Argyll and some of the islands.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA fine end to the day and
OL,12,Fstaying mainly dry overnight.
OL,13,FThickening cloud could bring patchy
OL,14,Frain to Argyll. Winds mostly light.
OL,15,
OL,16,CThursday:FMainly dry and bright with
OL,17,Fhazy sunshine and very warm or hot.
OL,18,FOccasional thicker cloud over Argyll
OL,19,Fcould give the odd burst of rain.
OL,20,FLight winds with sea breezes possible.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
